32
00:04:51,820 --> 00:04:57,710
Mr. Justice Bocari, one of an impending storm for the rule of law in Hong Kong.

33
00:04:57,990 --> 00:05:05,690
In light of the recent developments, I'm sad to say that the verification of his prophecy is now painfully self-evident.

34
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:14,250
15年後的漢諾威，是時候讓我們在這間議會提醒自己，卡諾原則的法治。

35
00:05:14,530 --> 00:05:27,740
the common law tradition, the rules of natural justice and procedural fairness, due process, habeas corpus, an independent judiciary, access to court for all, and an independent legal profession.

36
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:38,450
President, therein lay the foundations of the legal system we have, and I dare say, of the fundamental pillar under one country, two systems under the basic law.

37
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:47,300
這些非常原則形成一個明亮的星座，which has gone before us and guided our steps through an age of transition and reformation.

38
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:56,880
The Hong Kong people helped founded this special administrative region. We've helped crafted a constitution known as the Basic Law, and in this constitution.

39
00:05:57,390 --> 00:06:13,220
came the powers that were bestowed on our government. We've made it an executive government subject to checks and balances. We've defined its authority. We've restrained it to the exercise of such powers as are granted to it by the law, and we've not stopped there.

40
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:24,340
Who then shall construe this grant of power under the constitution? Who shall interpret this constitution? With whom do we repose this right of deciding on the powers of government?

41
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:36,000
Are we at the complete mercy of state discretion and state construction of our constitution, President? If we are, then in vain will be our attempt to maintain and protect our constitution.

42
00:06:36,330 --> 00:06:42,890
在憲法本身，一個proper and suitable mode of tribunal for settling questions of law have been established.

43
00:06:43,380 --> 00:06:54,360
條19條《基本法》明確指出，香港特別行政區將享有獨立的司法權力，包括終審權力。

44
00:06:54,650 --> 00:07:10,970
Apart from cases involving acts of state defence and foreign affairs, our courts have jurisdiction over all cases, and that their judgment shall be final. The constitution has itself pointed out, ordained and established the authority of our courts.

45
00:07:11,970 --> 00:07:28,400
The rule of democracy, the rule of law and democracy must go hand in hand. For democracy may disarm an oligarchy, a privileged class, but it can still crush individuals as merciless as any dictator can if we live without the rule of law.

46
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:39,150
The rule of law is what makes Hong Kong shine as the gem under one country, two systems. The rule of law is what make our nation not only great, but shall transform it into a good and moral one.

47
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:49,180
Our present cause is to protect and treasure the rule of law in Hong Kong, so that when the national impetus for change arrives, what we have in Hong Kong shall shine in the rest of our nation.

48
00:07:49,460 --> 00:08:04,040
這是非常任務，交給我們。讓我們回顧我們的國家和我們的路徑，並提升我們自己成為純潔和無私的愛國者，並驅動我們的國家走向一個公正和平的國家。

49
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:24,330
我知有許多認為時光已去，當一個人可以訴諸那些高貴和正直的衝動，那是曾經是我們性格的主軸和元素。然而，我認為有機會去指導我們國家的發展，去影響我們人民的命運，如果曾經是我們的榮譽野心，現在比以往更為重要。

50
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:27,250
must be so at the moment which we are speaking.

51
00:08:27,530 --> 00:08:47,540
這是個時刻，當法治的基礎受到威脅，來自那些不同意其基本前提的人。他們是法治的敵人，他們代表著威脅我們最珍視的東西的強大勢力。他們是毫無良知的人，只相信權力的殘暴。

52
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:49,530
無憲法束縛。

53
00:08:49,940 --> 00:09:01,190
Whether this threat is real or imagined, as some would blindly try to argue today, we must nevertheless safeguard the rule of law with all our might and with all our strength, President.

54
00:09:01,480 --> 00:09:14,120
For history shall blame us for our false sense of complacency. Should we allow the rule of law to fade, to slip away, and to leave its foundations broken and unrepaired, whilst under our guard?

55
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:23,640
我們必須繼續提供充足的資源，以支持我們司法機構和法官的工作，以保護他們的地位，以 safeguard 他們獨立的司法角色。

56
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:33,790
We must ensure access to justice for all, irrespective of one's economic condition. Hence, the need to continue to expand both civil and criminal legal aid.

57
00:09:34,070 --> 00:09:52,790
justice ought to extend her protection with rigid impartiality to the rich and to the poor, to the powerful and to the humble, and likewise the independence of our legal profession must also be guarded against any infiltration. A healthy and independent legal profession is key to maintaining the rule of law in Hong Kong.

58
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:54,500
主席。

59
00:09:54,920 --> 00:10:14,930
有政治家在這個議會，男人和女人，有抱有野心，到高公職的榮譽。這些是同樣的男人，現在被壓入一個溝，從而他們既不能逃脱，也不能後退，持有高公職，但維持在他們的現存判決，不。

60
00:10:14,930 --> 00:10:18,700
Harmonise well with their early opinions under a different role.

61
00:10:19,630 --> 00:10:39,640
May I remind those that the rule of law does not change depending on one's role or standpoint. The principles of rule of law do not change no matter where one is stationed in life. Be you now speaking as the chairman of the bar, the secretary for justice, a member of the legal profession, or an ordinary citizen seeking a day in court.

62
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:44,710
No, the impartial and fair scales of justice do not change.

63
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:45,970
主席。

64
00:10:46,850 --> 00:10:51,940
我 contemplate the progress of the rule of law in this nation will be slow and painful.

65
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:55,740
但我 look forward to it with perfect composure and confidence.

66
00:10:56,020 --> 00:11:11,030
為確立法治為我們國家的原則，從事前起，必須維護我們的憲法，藉由獨立的司法機關，並從其利益的確立，將會惠及整個國家的人民。

67
00:11:11,310 --> 00:11:15,190
